<BaseLayout
  title="Updates · America's School Trust Library"
  description="What's new in the library."
  sourceId="updates"
>
  <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none prose-a:text-blue-700 prose-a:underline">
    <h1>Updates</h1>
    <p class="kicker">A chronological log of significant additions and changes to the library.</p>

    <h2>May 2026</h2>

    <h3>Library renamed and rebranded as America's School Trust Library</h3>
    <p>
      <em>Late May 2026.</em> The site renamed from "Schools of the Republic" to "America's
      School Trust Library" with the tagline "An evidentiary archive of America's school trust
      lands and funds." New canonical domain at schooltrusts.net. The book remains titled
      <em>Schools of the Republic</em> (Sullivan &amp; Bird, 2025).
    </p>

    <h3>Reading Room restructured with content cards</h3>
    <p>
      <em>Late May 2026.</em> Each major content object — encyclopedia, white papers, vision
      essay, bibliography entries — now lives in its own dossier-style card with cover,
      abstract, and annotated table of contents.
    </p>

    <h3>Bibliography section added</h3>
    <p>
      <em>Late May 2026.</em> Foundational works on America's school trust lands now visible
      in the Reading Room. Initial entries include Fletcher Harper Swift's 1911 study (the
      seminal reference), the Hawk 2018 Oregon thesis, Puter &amp; Stevens 1908
      <em>Looters of the Public Domain</em>, and Heidelberg's 2014 paper.
    </p>

    <h3>Visual identity rebuilt</h3>
    <p>
      <em>Mid-May 2026.</em> Site rebuilt with archival-paper background, Source Serif 4
      typography, the PLSS-grid wordmark, and per-room subtle accents. Layout primitives
      (chapter openers, pull quotes, dossier cards, archival dividers, confidence badges) are
      now part of the design system.
    </p>

    <h3>Library opened</h3>
    <p>
      <em>Early May 2026.</em> Three rooms launched: Reading Room (encyclopedia, Sacred
      Compact, Vision), Atlas (four-lens choropleth), Counting House (50-row sortable
      financial table). Initial substrate: encyclopedia v1.3 (~45,000 words across 50
      states), Sacred Compact white paper v5.0 (~70 pages, 207 footnotes), Vision v2 ("The
      Eighth Anchor"). Domain at the time: schooltrusts.net.
    </p>

    <hr class="archival-divider" />

    <p>
      This page is the library's running changelog. New entries appear at the top of the
      relevant month. For the substrate's underlying version history, see the
      <a href="https://github.com/dave-schooltrustlands/schooltrustlands-encyclopedia"
        >GitHub repository</a
      >.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
